    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-02-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="559"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">411.19 L 22/957</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Panaman Chargé</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lefevre</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-02-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1921</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note D–No. 67 of February 8, 1921, in which, under instructions from your
                    Government and on the ground that the Government of the <pb facs="0716" n="620"
                        xml:id="pg_620"/> United States has recently taken over private property on
                    Taboga Island and in Las Minas Bay, Province of Colon, you make application for
                    the reestablishment of the Mixed Claims Commission referred to in Articles VI
                    and XV of the Treaty of 1903.</p>
                <p>In reply I beg to advise you that the matter has been taken up with the
                    appropriate branch of this Government and will be given due consideration, after
                    which the Department will take pleasure in advising you further.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norman H. Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Under Secretary</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
